Query GDC for cases

Query GDC for cases

case_fields(primary = TRUE)

cases(..., token = NULL, fields = case_fields())

Arguments

primary
logical(1) when TRUE (default) return commonly populated field names. Otherwise, return all field names defined in the API.
token
(optional) character(1) security token allowing access to restricted data. See https://docs.gdc.cancer.gov/API/Users_Guide/Getting_Started/#authentication.
fields
character() vector of requested fields. See case_fields() for defined fields.
…
(optional) additional parameters influence case selection. See parameters.

Examples

cases <- cases()
#> GET request uri:
#> https://gdc-api.nci.nih.gov/cases?format=JSON&pretty=FALSE&fields=sample_ids,portion_ids,submitter_portion_ids,created_datetime,submitter_aliquot_ids,updated_datetime,submitter_analyte_ids,analyte_ids,submitter_id,case_id,state,aliquot_ids,slide_ids,submitter_sample_ids&size=10&from=1
cases

#> cases: 10
#> names:

#> GET request uri:
#> https://gdc-api.nci.nih.gov/cases?format=JSON&pretty=FALSE&fields=case_id,submitter_id&size=10&from=1&sort=submitter_id:asc
